content: #StardewValley has ONE CAR in the whole town; you never need it to travel within the town. In fact, the town has no obvious roads for a car to travel upon (there are buses to facilitate going to different environments in the game, but not commonly used for core gameplay). Basically, #CarsFuckingSuck and should #GoDie; while they've made travel to Grandma's for #Thanksgiving faster, Grandma probably wouldn't even be that far away if cars never happened; how'd she get so far? Also roads are nasty.

content:
Irgendeine Putenmastanlage irgendwo in Deutschland, Thanksgiving 2023.

Sie liegt abseits, ohne Nachbarn. Hier schaut niemand zufällig hinein. 5000 Puten sind in jeder der Hallen eingesperrt, als „Mastputen“. Nach 21 Wochen Mast sollen sie 21 Kilo wiegen - und #Putenfleisch werden.

Für zwei Verzweifelte aus dieser Mastanlage gibt es eine Zukunft, während die anderen 20.000 Puten vielleicht jetzt schon tot sind.

(ℹ️ Kompletter Post auf FB & Insta)

content:
Ein Akt der Befreiung: #Puten an #Thanksgiving retten. 🌿 🦃

„Allein zu Thanksgiving werden jedes Jahr 46 Millionen Puten aufgezogen und geschlachtet. Wir beschlossen noch am selben Tag, dagegen Stellung zu beziehen.

In einer traurigen Halle mit künstlichem Licht, in der das Summen der Maschinen, starker Gestank und die Menge unzähliger Tiere den Alltag bestimmen, retteten wir zwei Puten, denen wir die Namen „Wendy“ und „Ashley“ gaben.

Ihre Befreiung erinnert uns daran, dass jedes Tier das Recht auf sein Leben hat. Ihre Geschichte erinnert uns daran, dass jede Rettung ein Schritt in eine Welt ist, in der Tiere respektiert werden. Es ist eine Erinnerung an unsere Verantwortung, für diejenigen einzutreten, die uns brauchen.“

In den nächsten Tagen veröffentlichen wir mehr Details zu der #Recherche und zu Wendys und Ashleys neuem Leben.

content:
Just marathoned through #Sekiro over the #Thanksgiving break and what a game! I thoroughly enjoyed the enhanced combat mechanics and slimmed down mechanics.

I was never one to really take advantage of the RPG elements of #FromSoftware games, so trimming all that mechanical fat for a more focused combat experience is exactly what I wanted. Mikiri counters and jump stomps add so much despite being such simple mechanics.

Genichiro Ashina is definitely one of my new favorite boss fights and the lightning counters just feel AMAZING to land. Absolutely loved the experience.

I don't think it unseats #Bloodborne as my favorite #SoulsLike, but it comes damn close.

content:
We usually go out for #Thanksgiving #dinner and then I'll make a #turkey with sides sometime later. Because this is the time of year when stores will sell you a turkey for $0.29/pound with minimum purchase or whatever, which translates to about $4 for a 12-15 pound bird. For two people, that's a big commitment. But what a deal!

This year I have decided the traditional sides will be collards, acorn squash stuffed with wild rice and topped with cheese, and kala chana masala. Because I said so.

content:
My aunt hosted Thanksgiving at her home and everything was elevated with the addition of sunlight streaming through the windows. (A welcome detail as it has been so overcast of late.)

I brought coleslaw and deviled eggs to add the abundance of dishes from everyone — turkey, ham, green bean casserole, sweet potatoes, stuffing, mac and cheese, mashed potatoes, gravy, rolls. ALL THE THINGS — and everything was awesome.

Went back for a second plate of sides and regret not bringing home a container with leftovers.

I somehow made room for desserts. A gluten free chocolate cake was my favorite with a tie for Yale’s chocolate pecan pie and an egg nog bundt cake as runner up.

Side note about deviled eggs: I have tried every method (short of forceful blowing) to peel hard boiled eggs and have come to believe two things:

  1. It doesn’t matter. Hard boiled eggs are finicky and will be easy or difficult to peel based on variables unknown.
  2. Even ugly deviled eggs taste great.

Two more points unrelated to egg preparation:

  1. I look like a giant in the above photo. (I don’t feel tall until I see it.)
  2. We need more get togethers centered around gratitude (that are also potlucks.)

https://chrisglass.com/2023/11/23/thanksgiving-at-aprils/

#Adam #AuntApril #family #Joshua #sayCheese #Thanksgiving #Yale

content:
A vegetarian harvest feast with the family.

Mushroom-rice stuffing, smoked tofu noodle casserole, mashed potatoes, cranberries with apples and oranges, and a dinner roll. Sweet potato pie to come.

Because it was a small gathering this year, I had each family member choose a favorite dish and those were the only dishes that I made. (No one chose the dinner roll, I bought those pre-made.) Turns out that everyone really likes carbs! And who can blame them?

#vegetarian #food #Thanksgiving

card.title: Thanksgiving, good food, and some snow
card.description: Welcome to Blood Soaked and Blind, a weekly newsletter from the author Matthew R. Taylor. I had a great Thanksgiving break last week. We got everything done outside and inside the house and ready to go for winter. Cleaning out gutters, mulching leaves, putting the mower away in storage and firing up the snowblower, all of that kind of fun stuff. And, glad we got all of that done. Saturday night into Sunday morning we got 3 1/2 inches of snow. So Sunday morning was spent shoveling the driveway and sidewalks and getting all of that cleaned up. Yup, welcome to living in Iowa. We also had some great food on Thanksgiving at my sister-in-law's house. Enjoyed stuffing myself and visiting with family. Also spent the week just spending time together, hanging out and relaxing. It really was a great five days off. Now it's back to reality. My wife is at work, and I miss her greatly, the kids are back to school, and I am zooming around the house getting everything done I need to get done, then sitting down to finally get some writing work done.

@3goodthings

#Thanksgiving Day was relatively drama free.

Managed to avoid anything resembling retail activity on #BlackFriday. One of the shopping malls near me had to close its doors because there were too many people inside. NO THANKS.

Highlight of the long weekend was revisiting The Walnut Room in the former Marshall Field & Co (now Macy's) on State Street in downtown #Chicago, Illinois, USA. Such a treat to have a meal under the big tree in a historic building.

content:
Seeing friends of mine on their way to Las Vegas or already there for Amazon’s AWS re.Invent conference makes me thankful that my schedule is devoid of business travel this week, even if solo travel for work can seem blissfully easy compared to family travel for Thanksgiving.

11/22/2023: Microsoft Rate Hikes for Bing Use May Put This Google Alternative Out of Business, PCMag

Ecosia CEO Christian Kroll revealed enough uncomplimentary things about Microsoft and Google when I interviewed him at Web Summit that I had to give those companies a chance to respond–and then the former did little with that opportunity while the latter didn’t answer my query at all.

11/22/2023: FCC Chair: Let’s Terminate Pay TV’s Early-Termination Fees, PCMag

I’m no fan of early-termination fees, having had to eat a $300-plus “ETF” to get away from a service contract with Sprint and move to T-Mobile in 2013, before T-Mo began covering those penalties for customers who switched from other carriers. But FCC chair Jessica Rosenworcel’s proposal only takes aim at them in cable and satellite TV, not in the far more essential category of broadband.

https://robpegoraro.com/2023/11/26/weekly-output-competing-with-google-fcc-vs-tv-etfs/

#Bing #ChristianKroll #earlyTerminationFees #Ecosia #ETF #FCC #GoogleCompetition #JessicaRosenworcel #payTV #Thanksgiving #WebSummit

card.title: Vatican Manuscripts Added Week 47 of 2023
card.description: A total of ninety-eight manuscripts were digitized this week into the Vatican repositories.  The distribution of works is back to the most recent pattern, with a massive forty-two coming from Pal.gr.  This brings the collection to 357 volumes uploaded into the Vatican repositories of the 400 that are available at Heidelberg, almost 90% coverage.  Hopefull...

content:
@KetoPlus
Did we all survive Thanksgiving, our eating plans intact?

Here's how I got through mine: I made my own keto rolls, walked right past the stuffing and sweet potato casserole, ate turkey and green beans and some mashed (real) potatoes with a LITTLE gravy, and had a sliver of pumpkin pie. And I fasted for 24 hours before and after. Absolutely no harm done!

The last few days since then our 3 grands have been with us, and of course breakfast cereals and Doritos make up a large part of their diets. I ate normally (MY normal) throughout though, and did fine. They were keto days, and today I'm back on animal-based.

Feel free to share if you want to, but no pressure :).

#lowcarb #keto #ketovore #carnivore #diet #Thanksgiving
